{"lemma":"دَمٌ","slug":"دَمٌ","root":"د.م.#","root_slug":"د-م-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-م-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَم","root":"دمو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13159"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to coat, to smear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to paint, to daub, to dye, to tint"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَمَّ (damma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ointment, salve, unguent, liniment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paint"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pigment, dye"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blood","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cat; wild cat","tags":["Yemen"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Afroasiatic *dam-\nProto-Semitic *dam-\nArabic دم\nInherited from Proto-Semitic *dam-, from Proto-Afroasiatic *dam-.\n\nSuggested by Hommel as inherited from a Proto-Semitic *dimm- (“wild cat”), but presumably borrowed from Ge'ez ድመት (dəmmat), because this is a Lockwort rare in literary Arabic and appears in the dialects only in northwest Yemen, whereas it overspreads all Ethiopian Semitic as the word for the cat; the compared Akkadian 𒁺𒈠𒈬 (du-ma-mu /⁠dumāmu, tumāmu⁠/, “leopard”) is considered probably a foreign borrowing.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/dam.ma/","/damm/","/dam/","/dimm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13159","headword_ar":"دَمٌ","root":"(dmw or dmY)","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAT","text_ar":"اَخْلَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humours"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,) well known: (T, M, K:) accord. to some, (Msb,) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damawN","text_ar":"دَمَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) or it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damFY","text_ar":"دَمًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Zj, Mbr, S, M, Msb, K;) thus in the correct copies of the K; (TA; [in some copies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoYN","text_ar":"دَمْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaYN","text_ar":"دَمَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) though deviating from other words of the same form in respect of its pl. [which see below]; (Mbr, S;) as is shown by its dual, (Zj, M,) which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damayaAni","text_ar":"دَمَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,) whereby [also] the letter gone from it is shown to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mbr, S;) but it has also for its dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaAni","text_ar":"دَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, Msb, K;) and some of the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damawaAni","text_ar":"دَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) in which last, however, [accord. to ISd,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", though generally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and this original form is used by a poet, [namely, Hoseyn Ibn-El-Homám, accord. to one of my copies of the S,] in his saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falasonaA EalaY AlA^aEoqaAbi tadomaY kuluwmunaA\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      wal`kino EalaY A^aqodaAminaA yaqoTuru Ald~amaY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have not our wounds bleeding upon the heels; but upon our feet the blood drops"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoYN","text_ar":"دَمْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, T, S, M, Msb;) as is shown by its pls., (Sb, S,) which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaA='u","text_ar":"دِمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumiY~N","text_ar":"دُمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, M, K,) also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimiY~N","text_ar":"دِمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboYN","text_ar":"ظَبْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalowN","text_ar":"دَلْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have for their pls."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZibaA='u","text_ar":"ظِبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZubiY~N","text_ar":"ظُبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dilaA='N","text_ar":"دِلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duliY~N","text_ar":"دُلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for if it were like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafFA","text_ar":"قَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSFA","text_ar":"عَصًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would not have such pls. (Sb, S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~N","text_ar":"دَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ignored by Ks; but is used by poetic license; (M;) or it is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dm","text_ar":"دم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damapN","text_ar":"دَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more special signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the two words being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADapN","text_ar":"بَيَاضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADN","text_ar":"بَيَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [i. e.] it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion of blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) or it is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) accord. to IJ. (M.) The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumaY~N","text_ar":"دُمَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *uw damK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُو دَمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man seeking to obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosecuting for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the revenge of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu fulaAnK fiY vawobi fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَمُ فُلَانٍ فِى ثَوْبِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a saying of the Arabs, meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the slayer of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 632.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlhadomu Alhadomu","text_ar":"وَالهَدْمُ الهَدْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlhadama Alhadama","text_ar":"وَالهَدَمَ الهَدَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a saying of the Arabs, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thy blood be sought, my blood shall be sought; and if thy blood go for nought, my blood shall go for nought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the latter reading, as is said in the Nh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and where thou shalt be buried, I will be buried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine abode shall be mine abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdm","text_ar":"هدم"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumoyapN","text_ar":"دُمْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlA^axawayoni","text_ar":"دَمُ الاَخَوَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The red, resinous, inspissated juice called dragon's blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanodamu","text_ar":"العَنْدَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlgazaAli","text_ar":"دَمُ الغَزَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZ~N","text_ar":"مَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"now called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaATiru Alamik~Y~u","text_ar":"القَاطِرُ الَمِكّىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [vulgarly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTor mak~ap","text_ar":"قَطْر مَكَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu Alv~uEobaAni","text_ar":"دَمُ الثُّعْبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwn siyaAwu$aAn","text_ar":"خُون سِيَاوُشَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlgizolaAni","text_ar":"دَمُ الغِزْلَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, having a beautiful blossom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgizolaAni","text_ar":"الغِزْلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumoyapu","text_ar":"دُمْيَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, having a blossom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu damK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ دَمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain red plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) mentioned by En-Nadr in “ The Book of Wild Animals. ” (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","T","K","Msb","S","Zj","Sb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}